This paper investigates the collective design and innovation processes in organizations using a custom-made computer-mediated collaboration platform. The study involves analyzing the idea generation activity among different background distribution conditions and visualizing the idea utility terrain on a 2D problem domain. The paper's focus on social network structure, machine learning algorithms, and visualization techniques suggests that it could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including Cybernetics (cs.CY), Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC), Sound and Music Computing (cs.SD), and Computation and Language (cs.CL). However, given the emphasis on collaboration and innovation, Cybernetics and Social and Information Networks are the most likely categories.
